68bool GcSafeCode::CanDeoptAt(Isolate* isolate, Address pc) const {
69 if (!UnsafeCastToCode()->uses_deoptimization_data()) return false;
70 Tagged<DeoptimizationData> deopt_data = DeoptimizationData::unchecked_cast(
71 UnsafeCastToCode()->unchecked_deoptimization_data());
72 Address code_start_address = instruction_start();
73 for (int i = 0; i < deopt_data->DeoptCount(); i++) {
74 if (deopt_data->Pc(i).value() == -1) continue;
75 Address address = code_start_address + deopt_data->Pc(i).value();
76 if (address == pc && deopt_data->GetBytecodeOffsetOrBuiltinContinuationId(
77 i) != BytecodeOffset::None()) {
78 return true;
79 }
80 }
81 return false;
82}

191Tagged<TrustedByteArray> Code::SourcePositionTable(
192 Isolate* isolate, Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi) const {
193 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
194
195 if (kind() == CodeKind::BASELINE) {
196 return sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate)->SourcePositionTable(isolate);
197 }
198
199 if (!has_source_position_table()) {
200 return *isolate->factory()->empty_trusted_byte_array();
201 }
202
203 return source_position_table();
204}

216Address Code::metadata_start() const {
217 if (has_instruction_stream()) {
218 static_assert(InstructionStream::kOnHeapBodyIsContiguous);
219 return instruction_start() + instruction_size();
220 }
221 // An embedded builtin. Remapping is irrelevant wrt the metadata section so
222 // we can simply use the global blob.
223 // TODO(jgruber): Consider adding this as a physical Code field to avoid the
224 // lookup. Alternatively, rename this (and callers) to camel-case to clarify
225 // it's more than a simple accessor.
226 static_assert(!InstructionStream::kOffHeapBodyIsContiguous);
227 return EmbeddedData::FromBlob().MetadataStartOf(builtin_id());
228}

230Address Code::InstructionStart(Isolate* isolate, Address pc) const {
231 if (V8_LIKELY(has_instruction_stream())) return instruction_start();
232 // Note we intentionally don't bounds-check that `pc` is within the returned
233 // instruction area.
234 return EmbeddedData::FromBlobForPc(isolate, pc)
235 .InstructionStartOf(builtin_id());
236}
237
238Address Code::InstructionEnd(Isolate* isolate, Address pc) const {
239 return InstructionStart(isolate, pc) + instruction_size();
240}

242int Code::GetOffsetFromInstructionStart(Isolate* isolate, Address pc) const {
243 const Address offset = pc - InstructionStart(isolate, pc);
244 DCHECK_LE(offset, instruction_size());
245 return static_cast<int>(offset);
246}

307bool Code::contains(Isolate* isolate, Address inner_pointer) const {
308 const Address start = InstructionStart(isolate, inner_pointer);
309 if (inner_pointer < start) return false;
310 return inner_pointer < start + instruction_size();
311}

328int Code::GetBytecodeOffsetForBaselinePC(Address baseline_pc,
329 Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecodes) {
330 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
331 CHECK(!is_baseline_trampoline_builtin());
332 if (is_baseline_leave_frame_builtin()) return kFunctionExitBytecodeOffset;
333 CHECK_EQ(kind(), CodeKind::BASELINE);
334 baseline::BytecodeOffsetIterator offset_iterator(
335 TrustedByteArray::cast(bytecode_offset_table()), bytecodes);
336 Address pc = baseline_pc - instruction_start();
337 offset_iterator.AdvanceToPCOffset(pc);
338 return offset_iterator.current_bytecode_offset();
339}
340
341uintptr_t Code::GetBaselinePCForBytecodeOffset(
342 int bytecode_offset, BytecodeToPCPosition position,
343 Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecodes) {
344 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
345 CHECK_EQ(kind(), CodeKind::BASELINE);
346 baseline::BytecodeOffsetIterator offset_iterator(
347 TrustedByteArray::cast(bytecode_offset_table()), bytecodes);
348 offset_iterator.AdvanceToBytecodeOffset(bytecode_offset);
349 uintptr_t pc = 0;
350 if (position == kPcAtStartOfBytecode) {
351 pc = offset_iterator.current_pc_start_offset();
352 } else {
353 DCHECK_EQ(position, kPcAtEndOfBytecode);
354 pc = offset_iterator.current_pc_end_offset();
355 }
356 return pc;
357}
358
359uintptr_t Code::GetBaselineStartPCForBytecodeOffset(
360 int bytecode_offset, Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecodes) {
361 return GetBaselinePCForBytecodeOffset(bytecode_offset, kPcAtStartOfBytecode,
362 bytecodes);
363}
364
365uintptr_t Code::GetBaselineEndPCForBytecodeOffset(
366 int bytecode_offset, Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecodes) {
367 return GetBaselinePCForBytecodeOffset(bytecode_offset, kPcAtEndOfBytecode,
368 bytecodes);
369}
370
371uintptr_t Code::GetBaselinePCForNextExecutedBytecode(
372 int bytecode_offset, Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecodes) {
373 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
374 CHECK_EQ(kind(), CodeKind::BASELINE);
375 baseline::BytecodeOffsetIterator offset_iterator(
376 TrustedByteArray::cast(bytecode_offset_table()), bytecodes);
377 Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecodes_handle(
378 reinterpret_cast<Address*>(&bytecodes));
379 interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator bytecode_iterator(bytecodes_handle,
380 bytecode_offset);
381 interpreter::Bytecode bytecode = bytecode_iterator.current_bytecode();
382 if (bytecode == interpreter::Bytecode::kJumpLoop) {
383 return GetBaselineStartPCForBytecodeOffset(
384 bytecode_iterator.GetJumpTargetOffset(), bytecodes);
385 } else {
386 DCHECK(!interpreter::Bytecodes::IsJump(bytecode));
387 DCHECK(!interpreter::Bytecodes::IsSwitch(bytecode));
388 DCHECK(!interpreter::Bytecodes::Returns(bytecode));
389 return GetBaselineEndPCForBytecodeOffset(bytecode_offset, bytecodes);
390 }
391}

393inline bool Code::checks_tiering_state() const {
394 bool checks_state = (builtin_id() == Builtin::kCompileLazy ||
395 builtin_id() == Builtin::kInterpreterEntryTrampoline ||
396 CodeKindCanTierUp(kind()));
397 return checks_state ||
398 (CodeKindCanDeoptimize(kind()) && marked_for_deoptimization());
399}

534bool Code::CanContainWeakObjects() {
535 return is_optimized_code() && can_have_weak_objects();
536}
537
538bool Code::IsWeakObject(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
539 return (CanContainWeakObjects() && IsWeakObjectInOptimizedCode(object));
540}
541
542bool Code::IsWeakObjectInOptimizedCode(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
543 Tagged<Map> map_object = object->map(kAcquireLoad);
544 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsMap(map_object)) {
545 return Map::cast(object)->CanTransition();
546 }
547 return InstanceTypeChecker::IsPropertyCell(map_object) ||
548 InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(map_object) ||
549 InstanceTypeChecker::IsContext(map_object);
550}
551
552bool Code::IsWeakObjectInDeoptimizationLiteralArray(Tagged<Object> object) {
553 // Maps must be strong because they can be used as part of the description for
554 // how to materialize an object upon deoptimization, in which case it is
555 // possible to reach the code that requires the Map without anything else
556 // holding a strong pointer to that Map.
557 return IsHeapObject(object) && !IsMap(object) &&
558 Code::IsWeakObjectInOptimizedCode(HeapObject::cast(object));
559}
560
561void Code::IterateDeoptimizationLiterals(RootVisitor* v) {
562 if (!uses_deoptimization_data()) {
563 DCHECK(kind() == CodeKind::BASELINE ||
564 !has_deoptimization_data_or_interpreter_data());
565 return;
566 }
567
568 auto deopt_data = DeoptimizationData::cast(deoptimization_data());
569 if (deopt_data->length() == 0) return;
570
571 Tagged<DeoptimizationLiteralArray> literals = deopt_data->LiteralArray();
572 const int literals_length = literals->length();
573 for (int i = 0; i < literals_length; ++i) {
574 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_literal = literals->get_raw(i);
575 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_literal;
576 if (maybe_literal.GetHeapObject(&heap_literal)) {
577 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, "deoptimization literal",
578 FullObjectSlot(&heap_literal));
579 }
580 }
581}

598bool Code::has_instruction_stream() const {
599#if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS) || !defined(V8_HOST_ARCH_64_BIT)
600 const uint32_t value = ReadField<uint32_t>(kInstructionStreamOffset);
601#else
602 const uint64_t value = ReadField<uint64_t>(kInstructionStreamOffset);
603#endif
604 SLOW_DCHECK(value == 0 || !InReadOnlySpace(*this));
605 return value != 0;
606}
607
608bool Code::has_instruction_stream(RelaxedLoadTag tag) const {
609#if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS) || !defined(V8_HOST_ARCH_64_BIT)
610 const uint32_t value =
611 RELAXED_READ_INT32_FIELD(*this, kInstructionStreamOffset);
612#else
613 const uint64_t value =
614 RELAXED_READ_INT64_FIELD(*this, kInstructionStreamOffset);
615#endif
616 SLOW_DCHECK(value == 0 || !InReadOnlySpace(*this));
617 return value != 0;
618}
619
620PtrComprCageBase Code::code_cage_base() const {
621#ifdef V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
622 return PtrComprCageBase(ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::base());
623#else // V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
624 // Without external code space: `code_cage_base == main_cage_base`. We can
625 // get the main cage base from any heap object, including objects in RO
626 // space.
627 return GetPtrComprCageBase(*this);
628#endif // V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
629}

667DEF_GETTER(Code, instruction_start, Address) {
668#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
669 return ReadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointerField(kSelfIndirectPointerOffset,
670 entrypoint_tag());
671#else
672 return ReadField<Address>(kInstructionStartOffset);
673#endif
674}
675
676void Code::set_instruction_start(IsolateForSandbox isolate, Address value) {
677#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
678 WriteCodeEntrypointViaCodePointerField(kSelfIndirectPointerOffset, value,
679 entrypoint_tag());
680#else
681 WriteField<Address>(kInstructionStartOffset, value);
682#endif
683}
684
685CodeEntrypointTag Code::entrypoint_tag() const {
686 switch (kind()) {
687 case CodeKind::BYTECODE_HANDLER:
688 return kBytecodeHandlerEntrypointTag;
689 case CodeKind::BUILTIN:
690 return Builtins::EntrypointTagFor(builtin_id());
691 case CodeKind::REGEXP:
692 return kRegExpEntrypointTag;
693 case CodeKind::WASM_FUNCTION:
694 case CodeKind::WASM_TO_CAPI_FUNCTION:
695 case CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION:
696 return kWasmEntrypointTag;
697 case CodeKind::JS_TO_WASM_FUNCTION:
698 return kJSEntrypointTag;
699 default:
700 // TODO(saelo): eventually we'll want this to be UNREACHABLE().
701 return kDefaultCodeEntrypointTag;
702 }
703}

709 set_instruction_start(isolate, code->instruction_start());

718void Code::ClearInstructionStartForSerialization(IsolateForSandbox isolate) {
719#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
720 // The instruction start is stored in this object's code pointer table.
721 WriteField<CodePointerHandle>(kSelfIndirectPointerOffset,
722 kNullCodePointerHandle);
723#else
724 set_instruction_start(isolate, kNullAddress);
725#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
726}

739RELAXED_UINT32_ACCESSORS(Code, flags, kFlagsOffset)
740
741void Code::initialize_flags(CodeKind kind, bool is_turbofanned,
742 int stack_slots) {
743 CHECK(0 <= stack_slots && stack_slots < StackSlotsField::kMax);
744 DCHECK(!CodeKindIsInterpretedJSFunction(kind));
745 uint32_t value = KindField::encode(kind) |
746 IsTurbofannedField::encode(is_turbofanned) |
747 StackSlotsField::encode(stack_slots);
748 static_assert(FIELD_SIZE(kFlagsOffset) == kInt32Size);
749 set_flags(value, kRelaxedStore);
750 DCHECK_IMPLIES(stack_slots != 0, uses_safepoint_table());
751 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!uses_safepoint_table(), stack_slots == 0);
752}
753
754// Ensure builtin_id field fits into int16_t, so that we can rely on sign
755// extension to convert int16_t{-1} to kNoBuiltinId.
756// If the asserts fail, update the code that use kBuiltinIdOffset below.
757static_assert(static_cast<int>(Builtin::kNoBuiltinId) == -1);
758static_assert(Builtins::kBuiltinCount < std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max());
759
760void Code::set_builtin_id(Builtin builtin_id) {
761 static_assert(FIELD_SIZE(kBuiltinIdOffset) == kInt16Size);
762 Relaxed_WriteField<int16_t>(kBuiltinIdOffset,
763 static_cast<int16_t>(builtin_id));
764}
765
766Builtin Code::builtin_id() const {
767 // Rely on sign-extension when converting int16_t to int to preserve
768 // kNoBuiltinId value.
769 static_assert(FIELD_SIZE(kBuiltinIdOffset) == kInt16Size);
770 static_assert(static_cast<int>(static_cast<int16_t>(Builtin::kNoBuiltinId)) ==
771 static_cast<int>(Builtin::kNoBuiltinId));
772 int value = ReadField<int16_t>(kBuiltinIdOffset);
773 return static_cast<Builtin>(value);
774}
775
776bool Code::is_builtin() const { return builtin_id() != Builtin::kNoBuiltinId; }

779 return CodeKindIsOptimizedJSFunction(kind());
780}
